==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Separatist
<hw>Sep`a*ra*tist</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>s⟦eacute⟧paratiste</ets>.]</ety> <def>One who withdraws or
separates himself; especially, one who withdraws from a church to which
he has belonged; a seceder from an established church; a dissenter; a
nonconformist; a schismatic; a sectary.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Heavy fines on divines who should preach in any meeting of
<qex>separatist</qex> .</q> <rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Separatistic</ent>⟦br⟧
